Six 5-10% drawdowns
Three 10-20% drawdowns
Two 20-30% drawdowns
One 30-40% drawdown
One 40-70% drawdown

All during a bull market.

In a global economy, users are actively seeking a secure way to conduct reliable cross-border transactions and remittance payments at a lower cost.

Stablecoins provide a clear solution.

Name: Coinbase
Content:
Can stablecoins change things for the globally underbanked?

Yup. Stablecoins can provide a secure store of value for users who may not have access, or have limited access, to traditional financial institutions like banks.

Name: Coinbase
Content:
In the diverse world of cryptocurrency, stablecoins stand out due to their unique promise: stability.

Policy decisions on stablecoins will dictate the future of the world’s digital financial system.

Raise your voice:https://coinbase.com/blog/stablecoins-are-part-of-the-future-of-money-and-theyre-already-here…

Name: Coinbase
Content:
Happy Stablecoin Week

Stablecoins are pivotal in advancing the real-world utility of crypto – they enable the future of programmable money.

What makes them great? Read on.

Name: Coinbase
Content:
How does the rest of the world use them?

In Argentina, protection against inflation and changing values is the primary driver of stablecoin ownership.

In Nigeria, it's to secure money in USD and be able to transact internationally more efficiently.

Name: Coinbase
Content:
Who owns stablecoins?

In the US, between 5-8% of all US adults (18+) own stablecoins. And 30% of people holding other cryptocurrencies also hold them.

Stablecoins are creating such a net-new demand for US Treasuries that they now represent the 16th largest holder of USTs.
